I think I'll write a follow-up blog post in regard to your questions.

There is an easier way to mock the UserAgent without using moq. It is really really easy.


public class HomeController {

protected virtual string UserAgent { get { return Request.UserAgent } }

....

} 

In Your Test:

public class TestHomeController {

public TestUserAgent {get;set;}

protected override string UserAgent { get { return TestuserAgent; }}

}

In your tests just use your TestHomeController and try not to override too much of the code your are testing. 

protected virtual is the best thing I've learned about unit testing, and has reduced the complexity of my test drastically.

